<BLOCK1><TI TOCID="II">JUDGMENT</TI>
<P>THIS APPLICATION made by The Commonwell Mutual Insurance Group (&ldquo;Commonwell&rdquo;) for a declaration that it does not have a duty to defend or indemnify the Respondent, Shayne Campbell in Court File Number 15-64061 initiated in the Ontario Superior Court of Justice at Ottawa was heard on May 29, 2018 at the Superior Court of Justice at 161 Elgin Street in Ottawa, in the presence of the lawyers for all parties, and the lawyer for Guarantee Company of North America (&ldquo;Guarantee&rdquo;), a named party in a parallel application.</P>
<P>ON READING THE NOTICE OF APPLICATION AND THE EVIDENCE FILED BY THE PARTIES, AND GUARANTEE, and on hearing the submissions of the lawyers for the parties, and the lawyer for Guarantee;</P>
<P>1. THIS COURT ORDERS that Commonwell's application is dismissed. There will be a declaration that Commonwell is required to provide Mr. Campbell with a defence and indemnity under its policy.</P>
<P>2. This declaration is without prejudice to any claims for contribution and indemnity as between defendants or insurers that may properly be made following judgment in the main action.</P>
<P><UNDER>MR. JUSTICE C. MACLEOD</UNDER></P></BLOCK1>
